OL,3,CTrains cancelled as drivers refuse to
OL,4,Cwork extra shifts on day of England
OL,5,Cmatch
OL,7,FMany train drivers and other crew
OL,8,Fmembers don't have Sunday working
OL,9,Fincluded in their contracts, with
OL,10,Fnumerous operators often relying on
OL,11,Fthem volunteering to work extra paid
OL,12,Fshifts to run timetabled services on
OL,13,Fthat day.
OL,15,FUnions must give 14 days' notice of
OL,16,Fofficial strike action, but drivers
OL,17,Fcan wait until just a handful of days
OL,18,Fin advance before confirming if they
OL,19,Fwill work on a rest day.
