OL,3,CTrains cancelled as drivers refuse to
OL,4,Cwork extra shifts on day of England
OL,5,Cmatch
OL,7,FIt axed at least 22 long-distance
OL,8,Fservices between London Paddington and
OL,9,Fsouth-west England, mostly from 4pm,
OL,10,Fwith England's match kicking off at
OL,11,F8pm.
OL,13,FSunday working is part of the usual
OL,14,Froster for drivers employed by LNER,
OL,15,Fbut the publicly-owned operator
OL,16,Fannounced shortly before 6pm on
OL,17,FSaturday it had cancelled 13 services
OL,18,Fon the following day ` including eight
OL,19,Fbetween London King's Cross and
OL,20,FEdinburgh ` due to "a shortage of
OL,21,Ftrain crew".
